:"recFyde4DlK98x0qv","target":"recxF6Nx69b2BrqS7","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recFyde4DlK98x0qv","target":"recL30tpeUpd8vHsg","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recFyde4DlK98x0qv","target":"rechxoZ6BVvibQbVa","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recFyde4DlK98x0qv","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recFyde4DlK98x0qv","target":"recAalC2QoLT7cJKN","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recFyde4DlK98x0qv","target":"recAIElabptRPkpxz","label":"event"},{"source":"recFyde4DlK98x0qv","target":"recGrIgOxWnxVl8h0","label":"event"},{"source":"recFyde4DlK98x0qv","target":"recXUXZhzA47ZRt5F","label":"event"},{"source":"recFyde4DlK98x0qv","target":"recuZhS7z4CatBOO0","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recMBSkN0DrdWPv2z","ref":"Acts.28.1","text":"And when they were escaped, then they knew that the island was called Melita.","year":62},{"id":"recqANlhwHwjoMTyw","ref":"Acts.28.2","text":"And the barbarous people shewed us no little kindness: for they kindled a fire, and received us every one, because of the present rain, and because of the cold.","year":62},{"id":"rec4eWPXJ5LjN0bDP","ref":"Acts.28.3","text":"And when Paul had gathered a bundle of sticks, and laid them on the fire, there came a viper out of the heat, and fastened on his hand.","year":62},{"id":"recwqVwdTrJj6bn2M","ref":"Acts.28.4","text":"And when the barbarians saw the venomous beast hang on his hand, they said among themselves, No doubt this man is a murderer, whom, though he hath escaped the sea, yet vengeance suffereth not to live.","year":62},{"id":"recRiSLhIqQ2njgP5","ref":"Acts.28.5","text":"And he shook off the beast into the fire, and felt no harm.","year":62},{"id":"rec6LA6ZHwa6weBES","ref":"Acts.28.6","text":"Howbeit they looked when he should have swollen, or fallen down dead suddenly: but after they had looked a great while, and saw no harm come to him, they changed their minds, and said that he was a god.","year":62},{"id":"recyABWsA7YDK8FN9","ref":"Acts.28.7","text":"In the same quarters were possessions of the chief man of the island, whose name was Publius; who received us, and lodged us three days courteously.","year":62},{"id":"recrphyDJvHtyuuRe","ref":"Acts.28.8","text":"And it came to pass, that the father of Publius lay sick of a fever and of a bloody flux: to whom Paul entered in, and prayed, and laid his hands on him, and healed him.","year":62}]}
